Italy Defeats France 22-21 in Six Nations Rugby; Wales Tops Ireland 19-13

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-03-12T19:04:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-12/italy-defeat-defending-champion-france-22-21-in-six-nations-rugby-match.html
  Italy  scored its first victory over
France in rugby’s Six Nations with a 22-21 triumph, while  Wales 
defeated Ireland 19-13.  Mirco Bergamasco kicked 17 points and Andrea Masi scored a
try in Rome as Italy ended an 11-match winless run in the
competition against France. Bergamasco booted five penalties,
including the winner with five minutes left, to help Italy to
its first win in this year’s competition.  Vincent Clerc and Morgan Parra touched down for defending
champion France, which suffered its second straight loss.  Michael Phillips scored a try and James Hook kicked 11
points to lead Wales past Ireland in Cardiff. Wales matches
unbeaten England, which plays Scotland tomorrow, with six points
atop the standings.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  